VALUES
(43, 5, 17, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Divine Work and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine work, as both passages emphasize the active role of Jesus in upholding creation and performing God''s will. In John 5:17, Jesus states, ''My Father worketh hitherto, and I work,'' which aligns with Hebrews 1:3''s depiction of Jesus sustaining all things.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 1, 2, 1, 2, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Work of God and Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of work in both passages. In John 5:17, Jesus states, ''My Father worketh hitherto,'' paralleling Genesis 2:2, where God ends His work. Both emphasize the ongoing nature of divine activity.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 23, 40, 26, 26, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Divine Work and Creation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine activity. Both passages emphasize God''s ongoing work in creation, with Jesus asserting his role alongside the Father in John 5:17, while Isaiah 40:26 speaks of God''s power in creating and naming the stars.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 43, 10, 30, 30, 'making himself equal with God', 'Equality with God', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' divine identity. In John 5:18, Jesus is accused of making himself equal with God, while in John 10:30, he explicitly states, ''I and my Father are one.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 43, 19, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Claims to Divinity', 'Both passages emphasize the claim of Jesus making himself equal with God. In John 5:18, he is accused of breaking the Sabbath and claiming God as his Father, while in John 19:7, the Jews assert he made himself the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 50, 2, 6, 6, 'making himself equal with God', 'Equality with God', 'This connection highlights the theme of equality with God in both passages. John 5:18 indicates Jesus made himself equal with God, while Philippians 2:6 states he thought it not robbery to be equal with God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 66, 22, 1, 1, 'God was his Father', 'Divine Authority and Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority, as Jesus claims equality with God in John 5:18, while Revelation 22:1 presents the throne of God and the Lamb, emphasizing their unity in providing life. Both passages underscore the significance of God''s presence and the life-giving nature of that authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 38, 13, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Shepherd and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of authority and the consequences of challenging it. In John 5:18, the claim of equality with God leads to hostility, while Zechariah 13:7 depicts the shepherd being struck, resulting in the scattering of the sheep, suggesting a similar rejection of divine authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 40, 12, 5, 5, 'broken the sabbath', 'Sabbath Observance and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the sabbath and its observance. John 5:18 discusses the breaking of the sabbath, while Matthew 12:5 highlights the priests'' actions on the sabbath, suggesting a deeper understanding of authority over the sabbath laws.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 66, 21, 22, 23, 'God was his Father', 'Divine Presence and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s presence and authority. In John 5:18, Jesus claims equality with God, while Revelation 21:22-23 emphasizes the direct presence of God and the Lamb as the ultimate light and temple.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 43, 12, 49, 49, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Son and the Father, highlighting that the Son acts based on the Father''s will. This connection illustrates the theme of obedience and divine command in Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.713, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 43, 8, 28, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Action', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus does nothing of himself, but acts in accordance with the Father. This connection highlights the unity between the Son and the Father in their actions and teachings.', 'theme', 0.6359999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Father and the Spirit. Both passages emphasize the divine power at work, with the Son doing what he sees the Father do and the Spirit raising Jesus and quickening believers.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 42, 21, 15, 15, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Empowerment', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine empowerment, where Jesus indicates that he acts based on the Father''s actions. Similarly, the promise in Luke emphasizes that wisdom and speech are given by God, enabling believers to respond effectively to adversaries.', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Creation and Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the relationship between God''s creative action and the Son''s dependence on the Father. Both passages emphasize the idea of doing according to the will and actions of God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 1, 1, 26, 26, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Divine Action and Creation', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Son and the creative authority of God. Both passages emphasize the idea of acting in accordance with a divine model, as the Son does what he sees the Father do, paralleling God''s intention to create humanity in His image.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 19, 50, 6, 6, 'the Son can do nothing of himself', 'Divine Action and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Son and the righteousness of God as judge. Both passages emphasize the divine authority and the alignment of actions with God''s will.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 43, 3, 35, 35, 'the Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Love and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the Father''s love for the Son and His authority. John 5:20 states that the Father shows the Son all things, while John 3:35 indicates that the Father has given all things into the Son''s hand.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 40, 3, 17, 17, 'the Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Sonship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. John 5:20 speaks of the Father''s love for the Son, while Matthew 3:17 declares the Son as beloved, highlighting their close bond.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 20, 8, 22, 31, 'the Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Relationship', 'Both passages emphasize the intimate relationship between the Father and the Son. John 5:20 speaks of the Father showing the Son all things, while Proverbs 8:30 describes the presence of Wisdom with the Lord, suggesting a shared divine partnership.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 43, 15, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Knowledge and Friendship', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge shared between the Father and the Son and between Jesus and his followers. Both passages emphasize the idea of revealing greater truths, with the Father showing the Son all things and Jesus making known all things he has heard from the Father.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 61, 1, 17, 17, 'the Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Sonship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. John 5:20 speaks of the Father''s love for the Son, while 2 Peter 1:17 highlights the Father''s declaration of Jesus as His beloved Son.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'all things that himself doeth', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that the Father reveals all things to the Son. This connection underscores the unique knowledge and authority of the Son in revealing the Father to others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 42, 10, 22, 22, 'all things that himself doeth', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that the Father reveals all things to the Son. This connection illustrates the unique knowledge and authority the Son possesses through this divine relationship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'quickeneth whom he will', 'Resurrection and Quickening Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of quickening the dead. John 5:21 speaks of the Son quickening whom he will, while Romans 8:11 discusses the Spirit quickening mortal bodies, linking the act of resurrection to divine agency.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 5, 32, 39, 39, 'quickeneth whom he will', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the authority to give life and take it away. John 5:21 speaks of the Son quickening whom he will, paralleling Deuteronomy 32:39''s declaration of God''s power to make alive.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 43, 11, 25, 25, 'the Son quickeneth whom he will', 'Resurrection and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of resurrection and life. John 5:21 speaks of the Son quickening whom he will, while John 11:25 identifies Jesus as the resurrection and the life, highlighting his authority over life and death.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 42, 7, 14, 15, 'quickeneth whom he will', 'Connection of Resurrection Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the act of raising the dead. John 5:21 states that the Son quickeneth whom he will, while Luke 7:14-15 illustrates this authority through the resurrection of the young man.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 44, 26, 8, 8, NULL, 'Resurrection and Divine Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages discuss God''s ability to raise the dead. John 5:21 emphasizes the Son''s role in quickening, while Acts 26:8 questions the incredibility of God''s power to raise the dead.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 21, 42, 8, 54, 55, 'quickeneth whom he will', 'Resurrection and Restoration', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing the dead back to life. John 5:21 speaks of the Son quickening whom he will, while Luke 8:54-55 describes Jesus restoring life to a girl.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
