(43, 5, 21, 43, 11, 43, 44, 'the Son quickeneth whom he will', 'Connection of Resurrection Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages emphasize the ability of Jesus to quicken the dead. In John 5:21, Jesus states that ''the Son quickeneth whom he will,'' which is exemplified in John 11:43-44 when He raises Lazarus from the dead.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 43, 5, 27, 27, 'all judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the Son for judgment. The first verse states that all judgment is committed to the Son, while the second specifies that he has been given authority to execute judgment.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 44, 17, 31, 31, 'all judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment by the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Son in judgment. John 5:22 states that all judgment is committed unto the Son, while Acts 17:31 refers to the man ordained to judge the world in righteousness.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'all judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment and Authority of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the authority of the Son in judgment and power. Both passages emphasize that all judgment and power are given to Jesus, establishing His role in divine authority.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 47, 5, 10, 10, 'judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment by Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment, as both passages emphasize the role of Christ in the judgment process. John 5:22 states that all judgment is committed to the Son, while 2 Corinthians 5:10 indicates that all must appear before the judgment seat of Christ.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 44, 10, 42, 42, NULL, 'Judgment by the Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus as the appointed judge. Both passages emphasize that judgment is entrusted to the Son, linking His authority in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 43, 9, 39, 39, 'all judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment and Spiritual Insight', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment as both passages emphasize the role of the Son in judgment. John 5:22 states that all judgment is committed to the Son, while John 9:39 indicates that Jesus came for judgment to reveal spiritual sight and blindness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 22, 45, 2, 16, 16, 'all judgment unto the Son', 'Judgment by Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus Christ in judgment. John 5:22 states that all judgment is committed unto the Son, while Romans 2:16 mentions God judging through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 62, 2, 23, 23, 'honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father', 'Honor and Acknowledgment of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of honoring or acknowledging the Son to have a relationship with the Father. John 5:23 states that not honoring the Son equates to not honoring the Father, while 1 John 2:23 reinforces that denying the Son means one does not have the Father.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 42, 10, 16, 16, 'honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father', 'Honor and Despise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between honoring and despising. In John 5:23, honoring the Son is equated with honoring the Father, while in Luke 10:16, despising the Son is linked to despising the Father.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father', 'Honor and Knowledge of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that honoring the Son is essential to knowing the Father. John 5:23 states that honoring the Son is equivalent to honoring the Father, while Matthew 11:27 reveals that knowledge of the Father comes through the Son.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 63, 1, 9, 9, 'honoureth not the Son', 'Honor and Doctrine Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of honoring the Son and abiding in His doctrine. The first verse states that honoring the Son is essential to honoring the Father, while the second verse indicates that one must abide in the doctrine of Christ to have both the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 43, 15, 23, 24, 'honoureth not the Son', 'Honor and Hatred of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between honoring the Son and the Father. The rejection of the Son in John 15:23-24 parallels the dishonor mentioned in John 5:23, indicating that to hate the Son is to also hate the Father.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 24, 17, 5, 7, 'honoureth not the Son', 'Trust and Honor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of trust and honor in relation to God. John 5:23 highlights the necessity of honoring the Son, while Jeremiah 17:5-7 contrasts those who trust in man with those who trust in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.384, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 23, 42, 12, 8, 9, 'honoureth not the Son', 'Honor and Confession of Christ', 'This connection highlights the importance of honoring the Son, as seen in John 5:23, and confessing Him before others, as stated in Luke 12:8-9. Both passages emphasize the relationship between acknowledging Jesus and one''s standing before God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'hath everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''everlasting life'' for those who believe. They highlight the consequences of belief and disbelief in relation to life and condemnation.', 'theme', 0.692, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 43, 6, 40, 40, 'hath everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting life for those who believe in the Son. They highlight the importance of faith in Jesus and the promise of resurrection at the last day.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 62, 5, 11, 13, 'hath everlasting life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life through belief in the Son of God. John 5:24 states that believers have passed from death unto life, while 1 John 5:11-13 affirms that having the Son equates to having life.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 45, 8, 1, 1, 'shall not come into condemnation', 'Connection of No Condemnation', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of condemnation for those who believe and follow Christ. John 5:24 speaks of passing from death to life, while Romans 8:1 assures no condemnation for those in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 52, 5, 9, 9, 'hath everlasting life', 'Connection of Salvation and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation and the avoidance of condemnation. John 5:24 speaks of passing from death to life, while 1 Thessalonians 5:9 highlights obtaining salvation and not being appointed to wrath.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 45, 10, 11, 13, 'believeth on him that sent me', 'Connection of Salvation Through Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief for salvation. John 5:24 speaks of having everlasting life through belief, while Romans 10:11-13 assures that whosoever believes will not be ashamed and will be saved.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 24, 62, 3, 14, 14, 'passed from death unto life', 'Passing from Death to Life', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from death to life. John 5:24 speaks of those who believe having everlasting life, while 1 John 3:14 states that love for brethren indicates this same transition.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 43, 5, 28, 28, 'the hour is coming', 'Connection of Resurrection Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the coming hour when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God. This connection highlights the promise of resurrection and life for those who respond to His call.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 49, 5, 14, 14, NULL, 'Awakening from Spiritual Death', 'This connection highlights the theme of awakening from death in both passages. John 5:25 speaks of the dead hearing the voice of the Son of God, while Ephesians 5:14 calls for those who sleep to arise from the dead.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 49, 2, 5, 5, 'the dead shall hear the voice', 'Resurrection and Spiritual Life', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being ''dead'' and receiving life through Christ. John 5:25 speaks of the dead hearing the voice of the Son of God, while Ephesians 2:5 discusses being quickened together with Christ, highlighting the transformative power of His voice and grace.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 43, 4, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Worship and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of an ''hour'' that signifies a transformative moment. In John 5:25, the dead hearing the voice of the Son of God parallels the true worshippers in John 4:23 who worship in spirit and truth, suggesting a profound awakening to divine presence.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 51, 2, 13, 13, NULL, 'Connection of Spiritual Resurrection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''dead'' and the subsequent ''quickening'' or revival. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Son of God to bring life to those who are spiritually dead.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 66, 3, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Life and Death', 'This connection highlights the contrast between spiritual life and death. John 5:25 speaks of the dead hearing the voice of the Son of God and living, while Revelation 3:1 addresses a church that has a name of life but is actually dead.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 25, 42, 9, 60, 60, 'the dead shall hear the voice', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'This connection highlights the theme of life and death in both passages. John 5:25 speaks of the dead hearing the voice of the Son of God and living, while Luke 9:60 contrasts the spiritually dead with those called to preach the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 43, 1, 4, 4, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life. John 5:26 states that the Son has life in himself, while John 1:4 declares that in him was life.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
