(43, 5, 30, 19, 40, 7, 8, 'the will of the Father which hath sent me', 'Connection of Divine Will', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking God''s will. John 5:30 speaks of doing the Father''s will, while Psalms 40:7-8 expresses delight in doing God''s will.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 30, 23, 11, 3, 4, 'my judgment is just', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of just judgment. John 5:30 highlights seeking the Father''s will in judgment, while Isaiah 11:3-4 describes a righteous judgment that does not rely on mere appearances.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 30, 45, 15, 3, 3, 'I seek not mine own will', 'Selflessness of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s selflessness in both passages. John 5:30 emphasizes seeking the will of the Father, while Romans 15:3 illustrates Christ not pleasing himself.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 30, 19, 96, 13, 13, NULL, 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment in both passages. John 5:30 emphasizes the just judgment of Jesus, while Psalms 96:13 speaks of the Lord judging the earth with righteousness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 31, 20, 27, 2, 2, 'my witness is not true', 'Self-Witness and Praise', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of external validation over self-promotion. John 5:31 states that self-witness is not true, while Proverbs 27:2 advises against praising oneself.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 31, 43, 8, 54, 54, 'my witness is not true', 'Self-Honor and Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of external validation over self-assertion. In John 5:31, Jesus states that self-witness is not true, while in John 8:54, he indicates that his honor comes from the Father, not himself.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 31, 43, 8, 13, 14, 'my witness is not true', 'Self-Witness and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of self-witness and its validity. In John 5:31, Jesus states that his self-witness is not true, while in John 8:13-14, he acknowledges bearing record of himself but asserts that his record is true.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 31, 66, 3, 14, 14, 'my witness is not true', 'Witness and Truth Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness and truth. In John 5:31, the concept of a true witness is introduced, while Revelation 3:14 refers to Jesus as the ''faithful and true witness,'' emphasizing the importance of authentic testimony.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 40, 3, 17, 17, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Beloved Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness to Jesus'' identity. In John 5:32, the witness is affirmed as true, while Matthew 3:17 presents God''s voice confirming Jesus as His beloved Son.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 43, 1, 33, 33, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness in both passages. John 5:32 speaks of a true witness, while John 1:33 refers to the Spirit descending as a sign of Jesus'' identity, serving as a divine witness to his role.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 43, 5, 36, 37, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Jesus'' Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness in both passages. In John 5:32, the idea of another witness is expanded in John 5:36-37, where the works of Jesus and the Father''s testimony serve as greater witnesses to His authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 62, 5, 6, 9, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of witness regarding Jesus Christ. John 5:32 speaks of a true witness, while 1 John 5:6-9 elaborates on the various witnesses, including the Spirit, water, and blood, affirming the truth of Christ''s identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 40, 17, 5, 5, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Beloved Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the emphasis on a true witness aligns with Matthew 17:5, where God affirms Jesus as His beloved Son, indicating His authority and truth.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 41, 1, 11, 11, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Divine Approval', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the emphasis on a true witness aligns with Mark 1:11, where God''s voice affirms Jesus as His beloved Son.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 42, 3, 22, 22, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the ''witness'' refers to the validation of Jesus'' identity, while in Luke 3:22, the Holy Spirit''s descent and the voice from heaven affirm Jesus as God''s Son.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 6, 8, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights the role of John as a witness. Both passages emphasize that John was sent to bear witness to the truth and the Light.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 15, 27, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John bearing witness to the truth about Jesus. John 5:33 refers to John''s testimony, while John 1:15-27 elaborates on his role in declaring Jesus'' identity and significance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 29, 34, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights John''s role as a witness to Jesus, as stated in both passages. John 5:33 refers to John''s testimony about the truth, while John 1:29-34 details John''s declaration of Jesus as the Lamb of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 3, 26, 36, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John bearing witness to the truth about Jesus. John 5:33 states that John ''bare witness unto the truth,'' while John 3:26-36 elaborates on John''s role in pointing to Jesus as the Messiah.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 42, 19, 41, 42, 'that ye might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation and Peace', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and the recognition of peace. In John 5:34, the emphasis is on the need for salvation, while in Luke 19:41-42, the lament over Jerusalem reflects a missed opportunity for peace and salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 43, 20, 31, 31, 'that ye might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through belief in Jesus. Both passages emphasize the purpose of their messages: to lead individuals to faith and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 62, 5, 9, 9, 'that ye might be saved', 'Witness and Testimony Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony, contrasting human witness with divine witness. Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s testimony regarding salvation and His Son.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 43, 5, 41, 41, 'I receive not testimony from man', 'Connection of Honor and Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the lack of dependence on human validation. The phrase ''I receive not'' in both verses highlights a rejection of human testimony and honor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 45, 10, 1, 1, 'that ye might be saved', 'Desire for Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the desire for salvation. John 5:34 expresses the purpose of Jesus'' words for the sake of salvation, while Romans 10:1 reveals Paul''s heartfelt prayer for Israel to be saved.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 46, 9, 22, 22, 'that ye might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation Efforts', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation, with John 5:34 highlighting the purpose of Jesus'' words to lead others to salvation, while 1 Corinthians 9:22 illustrates Paul''s adaptability in his mission to save others. This connection highlights the shared goal of bringing people to salvation through different means.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 54, 2, 3, 4, 'that ye might be saved', 'Salvation and Knowledge of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation present in both passages. John 5:34 emphasizes the purpose of Jesus'' words for salvation, while 1 Timothy 2:3-4 expresses God''s desire for all to be saved and to know the truth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 61, 1, 19, 19, NULL, 'Light in Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light shining in darkness. John 5:35 refers to a light that people rejoiced in, while 2 Peter 1:19 speaks of a light shining in a dark place, suggesting a shared theme of guidance and hope.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 40, 11, 11, 11, 'a burning and a shining light', 'John the Baptist''s Significance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of John the Baptist as a significant figure. John is described as a ''burning and a shining light'' in John 5:35, while Matthew 11:11 highlights his unparalleled greatness among those born of women.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 43, 1, 7, 8, 'rejoice in his light', 'Witness to the Light', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a witness to the Light. John the Baptist is described as a light in John 5:35, while John 1:7-8 explicitly states he came to bear witness of that Light.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 40, 3, 5, 7, 'rejoice in his light', 'Light and Baptism Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the response to a prophetic figure. John the Baptist is depicted as a light drawing people to repentance, while Jesus refers to him as a shining light, indicating his significance in guiding others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
