(43, 5, 35, 42, 1, 76, 77, 'burning and a shining light', 'Connection of Light and Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the role of John the Baptist as a prophetic figure who brings light and knowledge of salvation. Both passages emphasize the importance of preparing the way for the Lord and the illumination he provides.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 41, 6, 20, 20, 'light', 'Connection Between John and Mark', 'Both passages emphasize the positive reception of John the Baptist''s message. In John 5:35, he is described as a ''burning and a shining light,'' while Mark 6:20 notes that Herod ''heard him gladly,'' indicating a shared recognition of John''s significance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 35, 42, 1, 15, 17, 'burning and a shining light', 'Connection of Light and Preparation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a significant figure who brings light and prepares the people for the Lord. John the Baptist is depicted as a light in John 5:35, while Luke 1:15-17 describes him as one who turns hearts and prepares a people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 36, 43, 10, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Witness Through Works', 'Both passages emphasize that the works Jesus performs serve as a testimony to His divine mission. In each instance, the works are presented as evidence that He is sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 36, 43, 2, 23, 23, 'the works which the Father hath given me', 'Connection of Miracles and Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the works Jesus performed as a testament to his divine mission. In John 5:36, the ''works'' serve as a greater witness, while in John 2:23, the miracles lead many to believe in his name.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 36, 62, 5, 9, 9, 'the works which the Father hath given me', 'Witness of God and Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness in both passages. John 5:36 emphasizes the works of Jesus as a testimony of God''s sending, while 1 John 5:9 asserts that the witness of God regarding His Son is greater than human testimony.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 36, 40, 11, 4, 4, 'the works which the Father hath given me', 'Witness of Jesus'' Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness through works. In John 5:36, Jesus emphasizes that His works bear witness of Him, while in Matthew 11:4, He instructs to show John the things He does, which are the same works that testify to His identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 36, 44, 2, 22, 22, 'the works which the Father hath given me', 'Witness of Jesus'' Miracles', 'This connection highlights the affirmation of Jesus'' divine approval through His works. Both passages emphasize that the miracles and signs performed by Jesus serve as evidence of His divine mission and authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 43, 8, 18, 18, NULL, 'Witness of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of the Father bearing witness to Jesus. In John 5:37, it states that the Father hath borne witness of me, while John 8:18 reiterates that the Father that sent me beareth witness of me.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 43, 1, 18, 18, NULL, 'Witness of God and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme that no one has seen God, emphasizing the unique role of the Son in declaring Him. Both passages assert the absence of direct experience with God, reinforcing the idea that Jesus reveals the Father.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 40, 3, 17, 17, 'hath borne witness of me', 'Witness of the Father', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine testimony. In John 5:37, the Father bears witness to Jesus, while Matthew 3:17 presents the Father''s voice affirming Jesus as His Son.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 54, 1, 17, 17, 'neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his shape', 'Witness of the Invisible God', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s invisibility and the witness of His presence. In John 5:37, the emphasis on not seeing God''s shape parallels 1 Timothy 1:17''s description of God as ''invisible.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 54, 6, 16, 16, 'nor seen his shape', 'Witness of the Invisible God', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that God is unseen by humanity. John 5:37 states that no one has seen the Father, while 1 Timothy 6:16 reinforces this by declaring that no man hath seen God. This connection highlights the theme of God''s invisibility.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 62, 4, 12, 12, NULL, 'Witness of God and Love', 'Both passages emphasize that no one has seen God at any time. This connection highlights the idea that God''s presence is known through love and witness rather than physical sight.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 37, 62, 4, 20, 20, 'hath borne witness of me', 'Witness and Love Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of visibility and recognition of God. In John 5:37, the emphasis is on not having seen God, while 1 John 4:20 contrasts this by stating that one must love their brother, whom they have seen, to truly love God, whom they have not seen.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 62, 2, 14, 14, 'his word abiding in you', 'Connection of God''s Word Abiding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s word abiding in believers. In John 5:38, the lack of God''s word leads to disbelief, while 1 John 2:14 highlights that the word abides in the strong, enabling them to overcome evil.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 5, 6, 6, 9, 'his word abiding in you', 'Connection of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s word in the believer''s life. John 5:38 highlights the failure to have God''s word abiding in them, while Deuteronomy 6:6-9 instructs to keep His commandments in the heart and teach them diligently.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 43, 12, 44, 48, 'him ye believe not', 'Connection of Belief and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus and the consequences of rejecting his words. John 5:38 highlights the failure to believe in the one sent by God, while John 12:48 speaks of the judgment that comes from rejecting his words.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 6, 1, 8, 8, 'his word abiding in you', 'Connection of God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the importance of having God''s word within oneself. Both passages emphasize the necessity of internalizing scripture to achieve belief and success.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 20, 2, 1, 2, 'his word abiding in you', 'Connection of Receiving and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving and abiding in God''s words. John 5:38 highlights the failure to believe in the one sent by God, while Proverbs 2:1-2 encourages the reception and application of wisdom and commandments.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 20, 7, 1, 2, 'his word abiding in you', 'Connection of Commandments and Belief', 'This connection highlights the importance of keeping God''s words and commandments. Both passages emphasize the necessity of internalizing divine teachings to truly believe and live according to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 38, 23, 49, 7, 7, 'him ye believe not', 'Rejection of the Sent One', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection found in both passages. John 5:38 speaks of disbelief in the one sent by God, while Isaiah 49:7 refers to a servant whom man despises, indicating a parallel in the rejection of God''s chosen messengers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 42, 24, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Scriptures to Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the role of scriptures in testifying about Jesus. John 5:39 speaks of searching the scriptures for eternal life, while Luke 24:27 shows Jesus explaining how the scriptures concern him.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 42, 24, 44, 44, 'which testify of me', 'Connection of Testimony and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize that the scriptures testify of Jesus and must be fulfilled. John highlights the scriptures'' role in revealing eternal life through Him, while Luke points to the necessity of fulfillment in the law and prophets.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 61, 1, 19, 21, 'scriptures; for in them ye think ye have eternal life', 'Connection of Scripture and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of scripture as a source of truth. John 5:39 highlights that scriptures testify of Christ, while 2 Peter 1:19-21 affirms that prophecy is divinely inspired and should be heeded.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 44, 26, 22, 23, 'which testify of me', 'Connection of Testimony and Prophecy', 'This connection highlights how both passages emphasize the role of scripture in testifying about Christ. John 5:39 speaks of the scriptures testifying of Jesus, while Acts 26:22-23 mentions the prophets and Moses speaking about Christ''s suffering and resurrection.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 20, 8, 33, 34, 'search the scriptures', 'Wisdom and Instruction Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of seeking wisdom and understanding in both passages. John 5:39 emphasizes searching the scriptures for eternal life, while Proverbs 8:33-34 encourages listening to instruction and being blessed by it.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 40, 22, 29, 29, 'the scriptures', 'Understanding Scriptures and Error', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing the scriptures. John 5:39 highlights that the scriptures testify of Jesus, while Matthew 22:29 points out that ignorance of the scriptures leads to error.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 39, 23, 34, 16, 16, 'Search the scriptures', 'Searching the Scriptures', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking and reading the scriptures. John 5:39 encourages searching the scriptures for eternal life, while Isaiah 34:16 calls for seeking out the book of the Lord to find truth.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 43, 3, 19, 19, 'that ye might have life', 'Rejection of Light and Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejecting light and life. In John 5:40, the refusal to come to Jesus results in a lack of life, while John 3:19 describes a preference for darkness over light due to evil deeds.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
